description: The public portion of a Panamanian trial of more than two-dozen associates accused of helping some of the world’s richest people hide their wealth has come to an unexpectedly speedy conclusion.
title: Panama Papers trial's public portion comes to an unexpectedly speedy end

description: Rookie Wenceel Pérez hit a go-ahead two-out single in the ninth inning and the Detroit Tigers handed the Minnesota Twins their season-worst fifth straight loss, 5-4.
title: Tigers hand Twins season-worst 5th straight loss. Wenceel Pérez hits go-ahead single in 9th

description: PHILADELPHIA (AP) — Spencer Turnbull carried a no-hit bid into the seventh inning, Alex Bohm hit a pair of three-run homers and the Philadelphia Phillies beat the Chicago White Sox 7-0 on Friday night to extend their winning streak to four.
title: Phillies defeat White Sox 7-0 to extend their winning streak to four

description: The U.N. political chief says the year-old war in Sudan between rival generals vying for power has sparked “a crisis of epic proportions” fueled by weapons from foreign supporters who continue to flout U.N. sanctions aimed at helping end the conflict.
title: Sudan's horrific war is being fueled by weapons from foreign supporters of rival generals, UN says

description: J’den Cox walked off the mat after dropping a 2-2 decision to Kollin Moore at the U.S. Olympic wrestling trials on Friday night, leaving his shoes behind to a standing ovation.
title: Two-time world champ J’den Cox retires at US Olympic wrestling trials; 44-year-old reaches finals

description: Vinnie Pasquantino and MJ Melendez homered to help the Kansas City Royals beat Baltimore 9-4 and stop the Orioles’ four-game winning streak.
title: Pasquantino, Melendez homer as Royals win 9-4 and stop Orioles' 4-game winning streak

description: Summer Yates scored in the 26th minute and the Orlando Pride beat the San Diego Wave 1-0 in the National Women’s Soccer League.
title: Pride beat Wave 1-0 to remain undefeated in the NWSL

description: Dozens of women and men have searched a garbage dump and other sites outside Mexico’s capital for missing loved ones without the protection of authorities.
title: Mexican families searching for missing relatives unite to draw attention to their plight

description: Juan Soto hit a three-run homer into the right field second deck to cap a five-run seventh inning and the New York Yankees rallied to beat the Tampa Bay Rays 5-3.
title: Juan Soto's 3-run homer in 5-run 7th inning lifts Yankees over Rays 5-3

description: Travis d’Arnaud hit a go-ahead grand slam in the sixth inning for a three-homer game and the Braves beat the Texas Rangers 8-3 for their fifth straight win.
title: Braves' Travis d'Arnaud hits first 3 HRs of season, including go-ahead slam, in 8-3 win over Rangers

description: Justin Verlander allowed two runs and four hits over six innings to win his season debut for the Houston Astros 5-3 over the Washington Nationals.
title: Justin Verlander allows 2 runs over 6 innings in season debut for Astros in 5-3 win over Nats

description: Alec Bohm’s first homer of the game was hit the opposite way into the right-field seats. His second homer was lofted high into the left-center section.
title: Alec Bohm hits a pair of 3-run homers for Phillies against White Sox

description: Tyler Freeman hit a two-run homer and Steven Kwan and Andrés Giménez each drove in a pair, sending the Cleveland Guardians to a 10-2 victory over the Oakland Athletics.
title: Tyler Freeman hits a 2-run homer to help power the Guardians past the Athletics 10-2

description: Tyler Herro scored 24 points and was an assist shy of a triple-double, rookie Jaime Jaquez Jr. added 21 points and the Miami Heat grabbed the last spot in the Eastern Conference playoffs, running away from the Chicago Bulls 112-91 in a play-in tournament elimination game.
title: The Heat are headed to Boston after ousting the Bulls 112-91 in East play-in finale

description: Spencer Turnbull carried a no-hit bid into the seventh inning, Alex Bohm hit a pair of three-run homers and the Philadelphia Phillies beat the Chicago White Sox 7-0 to extend their winning streak to four.
title: Turnbull takes no-hit bid into 7th, Bohm hits pair of 3-run homers, Phillies beat White Sox 7-0

description: Brayan Bello allowed one hit in six innings as the Boston Red Sox breezed past the Pittsburgh Pirates 8-1. Bello struck out seven against two walks.
title: Brayan Bello allows 1 hit in 6 innings as Red Sox breeze past Pirates 8-1

description: Elly De La Cruz hit a three-run homer, Nick Lodolo pitched 6 1/3 innings of one-run ball for his second quality start since coming off the injured list and the Cincinnati Reds snapped a three-game skid with a 7-1 win over the Los Angeles Angels.
title: Elly De La Cruz slugs 3-run HR and Nick Lodolo works 6 strong innings as Reds beat Angels 7-1

description: Nelly Korda is one shot off the lead through 36 holes at the Chevron Championship as she seeks to tie an LPGA Tour record with her fifth straight win.
title: Nelly Korda 1 shot back through 36 holes at Chevron Championship as she chases 5th straight victory

description: The University of Southern California is further shaking up its commencement plans. The private university said Friday it has called off appearances by outside speakers and honorees.
title: USC cancels graduation keynote by filmmaker amid controversy over decision to drop student's speech

description: Justin Verlander allowed two runs and four hits over six innings in the three-time Cy Young Award winner’s season debut for the Houston Astros against the Washington Nationals.
title: Justin Verlander allows 2 runs over 6 innings in season debut for Astros

description: The U.N. World Food Program has agreed to help deliver aid for the starving civilians of Gaza once the U.S. military completes a pier for transporting the humanitarian assistance by sea.
title: US says a UN agency has agreed to help in distribution of aid to Gaza via sea route

description: Philadelphia’s Spencer Turnbull lost his bid for a second career no-hitter when he allowed a one-out single in the seventh inning to Gavin Sheets of the Chicago White Sox.
title: Phillies' Turnbull loses no-hit bid when Sheets singles for White Sox in 7th inning

description: Bill Tobin, a longtime NFL executive who helped construct the Chicago Bears’ famed 1985 championship team and later built a playoff team as the Indianapolis Colts’ general manager, has died.
title: Bill Tobin, a longtime NFL executive who helped build the 1985 Bears championship team, has died

description: Miles Russell is a 15-year-old freshman in high school. Now he's in the Korn Ferry Tour record book as the youngest player to make the cut in the 35-year history of the PGA Tour's top developmental circuit.
title: Miles Russell is 15. He sets Korn Ferry Tour record as the youngest player to make the cut

description: North Korea says it tested a “super-large” cruise missile warhead and a new anti-aircraft missile in a western coastal area as it expands its military capabilities in the face of deepening tensions with the United States and South Korea.
title: North Korea says it tested 'super-large' cruise missile warhead and new anti-aircraft missile
